'''TBL''' - Template for text encoding table pages on games.darkrepos.com

==Description==

This template creates standardized text table (TBL) documentation pages. TBL files map hexadecimal byte values to displayed characters, essential for ROM hacking and translation.

==Usage==

===Basic Usage===
<pre>
{{TBL}}
</pre>

===With Parameters===
<pre>
{{TBL
| encoding = Custom
| language = Japanese
| bits = 8
| description = Custom description
}}
</pre>

==Parameters==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Parameter !! Required !! Default !! Description
|-
| encoding || No || Custom || Encoding type (ASCII, JIS, Custom, etc.)
|-
| language || No || — || Primary language (English, Japanese, etc.)
|-
| bits || No || 8 || Bits per character (8, 16, variable)
|-
| description || No || (standard text) || Custom description for the page
|}

==TBL File Format==

Standard TBL file format uses:
* <code>XX=Y</code> - Single byte XX maps to character Y
* <code>XXXX=Y</code> - Two bytes XXXX map to character Y
* <code>XX=<end></code> - Control codes with descriptive names
* <code>*XX</code> - Dictionary/DTE entry marker

===Example TBL File===
<pre>
00=A
01=B
...
1A=Z
20=<space>
FE=<wait>
FF=<end>
</pre>

==Table Columns==

* '''Value''' - Hex byte value(s)
* '''Character''' - Displayed character or glyph
* '''Notes''' - Control code meaning, special usage, etc.

==Example Output==

{{TBL|encoding=Custom|language=English}}

| $00 || A ||
|-
| $1a || Z ||
|-
| $20 || (space) ||
|-
| $fe || — || Wait for input
|-
| $ff || — || End of string
|-
|}

